            </div>
            <div class="game-card">
                <h3>📅 Year Quiz</h3>
                <p>Guess the year of historical events. How close can you get?</p>
                <a href="/year-quiz" class="btn btn-primary">Play Now</a>
            </div>
            <div class="game-card">
                <h3>🤥 Who Lies?</h3>
                <p>Spot the lies among the truths. How is your fast thinking?</p>
                <a href="/lie-quiz" class="btn btn-primary">Play Now</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="quiz-night-guide">
        <h2>🎉 Host a Fun Quiz Night with Friends!</h2>
        <p class="lead">Transform your living room into the ultimate quiz arena and challenge your friends to an epic battle of wits!</p>
        
        <div class="guide-steps">
            <div class="guide-step">
                <h3>📋 Preparation (1-2 days before)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Invite your friends</strong> - Create a group chat and get everyone excited!</li>
                    <li><strong>Prepare at least 3 quizzes of each type</strong> - Sort Quiz, Year Quiz, and Who Lies? games</li>
                    <li><strong>Save the JSON files</strong> - Make sure all your quiz data is ready to go</li>
                    <li><strong>Set up your tech</strong> - Ensure you have a big screen or TV ready for casting</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="guide-step">
                <h3>🎮 Setup (30 minutes before)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Cast this page to your big screen</strong> - Use Chromecast, AirPlay, or HDMI cable</li>
                    <li><strong>Prepare buzzers or keyboards</strong> - Each team needs a way to signal their answers</li>
                    <li><strong>Set up scoring system</strong> - Whiteboard, paper, or digital score tracker</li>
                    <li><strong>Create teams</strong> - 2-4 people per team works best</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="guide-step">
                <h3>🍕 Food & Drinks</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Order or prepare snacks</strong> - Pizza, nachos, finger foods that won't distract from the game</li>
                    <li><strong>Provide drinks</strong> - Beer, wine, soft drinks, or whatever your group prefers</li>
                    <li><strong>Keep it simple</strong> - You want to focus on the quiz, not cooking!</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="guide-step">
                <h3>🏆 Game Rules</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Play locally</strong> - Everyone in the same room for maximum fun and banter</li>
                    <li><strong>Count points per team</strong> - Keep track of scores throughout the night</li>
                    <li><strong>Mix up the quiz types</strong> - Alternate between Sort Quiz, Year Quiz, and Who Lies?</li>
                    <li><strong>Add bonus rounds</strong> - Quick fire questions or team challenges</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="guide-step">
                <h3>🎊 The Grand Finale</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Announce the winner</strong> - Dramatic reveal of the final scores</li>
                    <li><strong>Let the winner host the next quiz night!</strong> - Keep the tradition going</li>
                    <li><strong>Take photos</strong> - Document the fun for future memories</li>
                    <li><strong>Plan the next one</strong> - The winner gets to choose the theme for next time</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="pro-tips">
            <h3>💡 Pro Tips</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Have a backup plan in case of technical issues</li>
                <li>Keep the energy high with music between rounds</li>
                <li>Consider themed nights (movies, sports, history, etc.)</li>
                <li>Don't forget to have fun - it's not about winning, it's about laughing together!</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

